news.title: TVS Emerald to acquire Radial IT Park phase II, III for over Rs 575 crore
news.para: TVS Emerald will acquire 43.59 lakh equity shares, and 7.25 lakh compulsorily convertible debentures, constituting 100 per cent of the issued and paid-up share capital of Radial (Phase II) IT Park Pvt Ltd for a consideration of Rs 234.33 crore, TVS Holdings said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: ED raids Agra-based real estate businessman’s residence over fraud case
news.para: The ED team arrived at 7 am and seized documents, laptops, and computers, which are currently being scrutinised. Prakhar Garg, who is facing 25 fraud cases, was not present at the residence.

news.title: Gurugram: Eight years on, MCG yet to take over maintenance of DLF phases 1-3
news.para: The case, filed by the Gurgaon Citizens Council, was to be heard on Monday but it could not take place and the next date was given for Feb 4.

news.title: I-T department raids 52 premises of builders and brokers in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: The investigation team seized Rs 3 crore in cash, including Rs 1.2 crore from another builder. They also confiscated a large number of documents, mobile phones, and computer hard disks.

news.title: TARC pledges full cooperation as Sebi launches financial audit
news.para: "Together as a team, we continue to build on the values that define TARC’s journey while extending our full cooperation to SEBI and the forensic auditors,” said Amar Sarin, MD & CEO, TARC Ltd.

news.title: Noida authority plans to demolish over 200 illegal buildings
news.para: The move came after the Authority issued final notices to owners, giving them 15 days to present their cases. With the deadline approaching, the Authority plans to raze the illegal structures if the owners fail to respond satisfactorily.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM allocates Rs 400 crore to speed up 'Kalaignarin Kanavu Illam' housing scheme
news.para: Houses under the scheme has a 360 sq ft built-up area, including a kitchen and construction materials such as cement and steel bars were being provided to beneficiaries at subsidised prices through the state-run TN Cements Corporation.

news.title: Endurance Technologies' MD buys bungalow for Rs 130 crore in Delhi
news.para: According to documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, the Jain paid ₹8.32 crore stamp duty for the transaction, which ranks among the costliest in New Delhi.

news.title: Trichy: Traders seek rollback of 18% GST on rent paid for commercial properties
news.para: The federation, which conducted a general body meeting in Trichy on Tuesday, also urged the state govt to withdraw the 6% annual hike proposed in property tax and the trade licence fee collected from commercial properties.

news.title: Karnataka government withdraws town and country planning amendment bill
news.para: Urban Development Minister Suresh BS informed the Assembly that the decision was made after identifying some flaws in the bill, though he did not elaborate on the specifics.

news.title: Rajasthan implements geo-fencing technology to combat illegal sand mining
news.para: An official said, "Geo-fencing will be instrumental in monitoring high-risk areas, while GPS tracking systems will be installed at check posts to enhance oversight. Furthermore, seized sand will be transported using the e-Ravanna system to maintain transparency."

news.title: House prices in UK to grow up to 3% in 2025: Halifax
news.para: "The uneven availability of properties for sale across the country, relative to demand ... continues to underpin prices," Amanda Bryden, head of Halifax mortgages, said.

news.title: Rent for residential properties in England rise 9.3% over year to November 2024
news.para: Private sector rents in England rose by 9.3% to an average of 1,362 pounds ($1,727.97) in the 12 months to November, the strongest increase in records dating back to 2015, the Office for National Statistics said.

news.title: Kalapataru Projects International raises about Rs 1,000 crore through share sale on QIP route
news.para: Kalpataru Projects International Ltd (KPIL) has raised about Rs 1,000 crore through issuance 83.26 lakh equity shares at Rs 1,201 per piece on qualified institutions placement (QIP) basis.

news.title: Indore: 31 brick kilns to be razed to make way for MR-12 road project
news.para: The Indore Development Authority (IDA) is constructing the 9.4 km long MR-12 road from the Bypass to Ujjain Road. Due to various obstacles, only 3.5 km of the road was completed so far.

news.title: Bill tabled in Karnataka assembly to replace MUDA with Mysuru development body
news.para: Unlike MUDA, which had all the legislators from Mysuru and the police commissioner as its members, the MDA will have only two legislators from Karnataka.

news.title: Sweden's SBB exchanges $2.9 billion debt, eyes lower leverage ahead
news.para: The group said bondholders had agreed to an exchange of debt valued at 2.78 billion euros ($2.92 billion) in return for new securities, part of an effort to overcome objections from some creditors to its restructuring.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet approves 30% land subsidy for multi-modal logistics parks
news.para: Officials said a company establishing a multi-modal logistics park will be given a 30% upfront land subsidy on plots leased by industrial development authorities or any state govt agency.

news.title: Sanghi Industries shares tumble nearly 13% on merger with Ambuja Cements
news.para: Adani Group will merge its recently acquired Sanghi Industries and Penna Cement with Ambuja Cements to consolidate cement operations in one unit, the conglomerate said Tuesday.

news.title: Sahiti Infratec Ventures & its promoters swindled Rs 842 crore from homebuyers: ED
news.para: In its prosecution complaint filed in the PMLA court recently, ED alleged that the total Rs 853 crore collected, Rs 214 crore involved cash transactions with funds diverted through multiple accounts.
